<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United states</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking, China</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-20"><hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2916.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In my dispatch No. 2901½, of the 2d
                            instant, I set out the terms of a settlement of the recent riot at
                            Chiang Pei which I had agreed on with the Tsung-li Yamên.</p>
                        <p>One of the stipulations was the payment of 500 taels as damages. This
                            amount had been wired me by the consul-general as the sum recommended by
                            our consul at Chung king, but it turned out that there was a telegraphic
                            error, and that the true sum was 5,000 taels. I informed the Yamên of
                            the mistake and demanded the latter sum.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Denby</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>